{
  "semi": true,
  "trailingComma": "es5",
  "singleQuote": true,
  "printWidth": 80,
  "tabWidth": 2,
  "endOfLine": "lf"
}

---

This file sets your formatting rules:

> semi: Enforce semicolons at the end of statements.

> trailingComma: Use trailing commas in ES5-valid places.

> singleQuote: Prefer single quotes for strings.

> printWidth: Wrap lines longer than 80 characters.

> tabWidth: Use 2 spaces per indent.

> endOfLine: Ensure consistent line endings.
